assignment3

Class Operator

  • java.lang.Object
    • assignment3.Operator

  • public class Operator
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an operator, i.e. an arithmetical operation that is performed on operands. Modified by me (Allison Schinagle) to conform with the Google Java style guide (more or less; 4 spaces instead of 2), and added documentation and a toString method, and uses my OpType enum instead of the one given, and constructs an OpType from a String. Inherits from Token, since an Operator is a kind of token.

      • compare

        public static int compare(Operator a,
                          Operator b)
        Compares the precedences of two Operators. If they're equal, returns 0, if Operator a has a lower precedence than Operator a, return -1, and if Operator a has a higher precedence than Operator b, return 1.
        Returns:
        an int representing whether two Operators are equal in precedence, or if one is less than or higher than the other
